==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Involuted
<hw>In"vo*lu`ted</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>involutus</ets>, p. p.
of <ets>involvere</ets>. See <er>Involve</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Rolled inward from the edges; -- said of leaves
in vernation, or of the petals of flowers in ⟦ae⟧stivation.</def>
<rj><au>Gray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Turned inward at the
margin, as the exterior lip of the Cyprea.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>Rolled inward spirally.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Involute</ent>⟦br⟧
